# Admin Dashboard Environment Variables

# ============ API CONFIGURATION ============
# CRITICAL for production - Must point to your deployed backend
# Development: http://localhost:5000/api
# Production: https://your-backend-domain.com/api
VITE_API_URL=https://aurie.onrender.com/api

# ============ DEPLOYMENT NOTES ============
# 1. This file is for documentation only - DO NOT commit actual .env to git
# 2. In production, set VITE_API_URL to your actual backend URL
# 3. Admin dashboard uses this URL for:
#    - Admin authentication (login)
#    - Viewing orders
#    - Viewing customers
#    - Managing products
#    - Real-time updates via Socket.io

# ============ ADMIN DEPLOY STEPS ============
# 1. Update VITE_API_URL to production backend
# 2. Run: npm run build (creates admin/dist/)
# 3. Deploy to production:
#    - Option 1: Vercel/Netlify (auto from git)
#    - Option 2: Docker container
#    - Option 3: Static hosting (S3, etc.)
#    - Option 4: Same server as backend (nginx)
